{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780906975550,"sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_p541bYRzDpA4ibMZIHjhiHmA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Review Quick Reference\n7: \n8: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: ### Purpose\n15: \n16: Use this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n17: \n18: ### When to Use\n19: \n20: - Looking up the canonical `/deep:start-review-loop` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n21: - Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n22: - Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n23: - Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n24: \n25: ### Commands\n26: \n27: | Command | Description |\n28: |---------|-------------|\n29: | `/deep:start-review-loop:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n30: | `/deep:start-review-loop:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n31: | `/deep:start-review-loop \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n32: \n33: ### Parameters\n34: \n35: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n36: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n37: | `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n38: | `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n39: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n40: | `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 2. WHEN TO USE\n45: \n46: | Scenario | Use |\n47: |----------|-----|\n48: | Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:start-review-loop` |\n49: | Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n50: | Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:start-review-loop:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n51: | Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:start-review-loop:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n52: | Deep technical investigation | `/deep:start-research-loop` (different skill) |\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n57: \n58: ```\n59: /deep:start-review-loop  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n60:     |                    |                      |\n61:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n62:     |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n63:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n64:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n65:     |                    |\n66:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n67:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n68:     |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n69:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 4. STATE FILES\n75: \n76: Review mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n77: \n78: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n79: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n80: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n81: | State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n82: | Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n83: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n84: | Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n85: | Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n86: | Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n87: | Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n88: \n89: ### Lifecycle Modes\n90: \n91: | Mode | Effect |\n92: |------|--------|\n93: | `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n94: | `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n95: | `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n96: | `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n101: \n102: | ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n103: |----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n104: | D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n105: | D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n106: | D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n107: | D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n112: \n113: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n114: |---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n115: | FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n116: | CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n117: | PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n118: \n119: ### Release Readiness\n120: \n121: `releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n122: \n123: | State | Meaning |\n124: |-------|---------|\n125: | `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n126: | `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n127: | `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n132: \n133: | Gate | Rule |\n134: |------|------|\n135: | Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n136: | Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n137: | Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n142: \n143: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n144: |--------|--------|-------------|\n145: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n146: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n147: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n148: \n149: **Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n150: \n151: **P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n156: \n157: Each @deep-review iteration:\n158: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n159: 2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n160: 3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n161: 4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n162: 5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n163: 6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n164: 7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n169: \n170: | # | Section | Purpose |\n171: |---|---------|---------|\n172: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n173: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n174: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n175: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n176: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n177: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n178: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n179: | 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n180: | 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n185: \n186: | Goal | Adjustment |\n187: |------|------------|\n188: | Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n189: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n190: | Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n191: | Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n196: \n197: | Problem | Fix |\n198: |---------|-----|\n199: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05 |\n200: | Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n201: | P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n202: | Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n203: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## 13. RELATED\n208: \n209: | Resource | Purpose |\n210: |----------|---------|\n211: | `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n212: | `sk-code-review` | Single-pass code review |\n213: | `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n214: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n215: | `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n216: \n217: For review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n218: - `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n219: - `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n220: - `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms\n\n(End of file - total 220 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nUse this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up the canonical `/deep:start-review-loop` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nUse this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up the canonical `/deep:start-review-loop` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n- Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n- Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n- Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n\n### Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:start-review-loop:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:start-review-loop:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:start-review-loop \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n\n---\n\n## 2. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:start-review-loop` |\n| Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n| Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:start-review-loop:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n| Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:start-review-loop:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n| Deep technical investigation | `/deep:start-research-loop` (different skill) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```\n/deep:start-review-loop  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE FILES\n\nReview mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n| State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n| Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n| Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n| Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n| Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n\n### Lifecycle Modes\n\n| Mode | Effect |\n|------|--------|\n| `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n| `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n| `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n| `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\n| ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n|----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n| D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n| D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n| D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n\n---\n\n## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Release Readiness\n\n`releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n| `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n| `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n| Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n| Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n\n**Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n\n**P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n\n---\n\n## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-review iteration:\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n\n---\n\n## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n| Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n\n---\n\n## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05 |\n| Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n| P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n| Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n\n---\n\n## 13. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n| `sk-code-review` | Single-pass code review |\n| `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n| `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n\nFor review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n- `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n- `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n- `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":220,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1780906975542,"end":1780906975548}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_026bcb7bde4a4d56016a267bdf839c81918255c47667796b1f"}},"id":"prt_ea653e12f0017nXedKiqKaEMY4","sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","messageID":"msg_ea65391be001soWxilxpMDrfUs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780906975628,"sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Kc9ddgsFytSyrTNYjpb1f0Rs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n34:   max_iterations: 7\n35:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n36: \n37: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n38: # CONTEXT LOADING\n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: context_loading:\n41:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n42:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n43:   mcp_integration:\n44:     tool: memory_context\n45:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n46:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n47:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n48:   behavior:\n49:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n50:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n51: \n52: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n53: # SKILL REFERENCE\n54: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n55: skill_reference:\n56:   skill: deep-review\n57:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md\n58:   references:\n59:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n60:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n61:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n62:   templates:\n63:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n64:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n65: \n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n68: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n69: agent_config:\n70:   agent: deep-review\n71:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n72:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n73:   mode: subagent\n74:   model: opus\n75:   leaf_only: true\n76:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n77:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n78:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n79: \n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: # STATE FILE PATHS\n82: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n83: state_paths:\n84:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n85:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n86:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n87:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n88:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n89:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n90:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n91:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n92:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n93:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n94:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n95:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n96:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n97:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n98:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n99:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n100:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n101:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n102:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n103:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n104:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n105:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n106:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n107:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n108:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n109:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n110: \n111: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n112: # WORKFLOW\n113: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n114: workflow:\n115: \n116:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n117:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n118:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n119:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n120:     if_present:\n121:       bind:\n122:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n123:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n124:         artifact_subfolder: null\n125:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n126:     if_absent:\n127:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n128:       outputs:\n129:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n130:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n131:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n132:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n133: \n134:   step_fanout_spawn:\n135:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n136:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n137:     instructions: |\n138:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n139:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n140:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n141:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n142:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n143:     sub_steps:\n144:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n145:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n146:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n147:         command: |\n148:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n149:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n150:             --loop-type review \\\n151:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n152:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n153:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n154:         wait_for_completion: true\n155:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n156:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n157:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n158:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n159:         dispatch:\n160:           agent: deep-review\n161:           model: opus\n162:           context: |\n163:             Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n164:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n165:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n166:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n167:               executor: native\n168:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n169:         wait_for_completion: true\n170: \n171:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n172:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n173:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n174:   phase_init:\n175:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n176:     steps:\n177: \n178:       step_preflight_contract:\n179:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n180:         verify:\n181:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n182:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n183:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n184:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n185:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n186: \n187:       step_create_directories:\n188:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n189:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n190: \n191:       step_detect_resource_map:\n192:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n193:         inspect:\n194:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n195:         classify:\n196:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n197:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n198:         outputs:\n199:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n200:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n201: \n202:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n203:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n204:         detect:\n205:           canonical_review_state:\n206:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n207:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n208:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n209:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n210:           legacy_review_state:\n211:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n212:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n213:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n214:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n215:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n216:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n217:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n218:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n219:           legacy_review_markers:\n220:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n221:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n222:         migrate_only:\n223:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n224:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n225:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n226:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n227:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n228:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n229:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n230:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n231:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n232:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n233:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n234:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n235: \n236:       step_acquire_lock:\n237:         action: \"Acquire the advisory lock defined by the spec_check_protocol before session classification\"\n238:         command: \"Open {state_paths.lock_file} with exclusive non-blocking advisory locking semantics; fail closed on contention.\"\n239:         note: \"macOS/BSD locking here is advisory. Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n240:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n241:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n242:         on_halt:\n243:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n244:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n245:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n246:         on_cancel:\n247:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n248:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n249:         on_workflow_exit:\n250:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n251:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n252: \n253:       step_classify_session:\n254:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n255:         inspect:\n256:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n257:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n258:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n259:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n260:         classify:\n261:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n262:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n263:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n264:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n265:         outputs:\n266:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n267:         on_resume:\n268:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n269:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n270:           skip_to: phase_loop\n271:         on_restart:\n272:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n273:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n274:           set:\n275:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n276:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n277:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n278:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n279:           skip_to: step_create_config\n280:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n281:         on_completed_session:\n282:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n283:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n284:         on_invalid_state:\n285:           halt: true\n286:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n287:         on_fresh:\n288:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n289: \n290:       step_scope_discovery:\n291:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n292:         resolve:\n293:           spec-folder: |\n294:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n295:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n296:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n297:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n298:           skill: |\n299:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n300:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n301:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n302:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n303:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n304:           agent: |\n305:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n306:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n307:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n308:           track: |\n309:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n310:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n311:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n312:           files: |\n313:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n314:             2. Validate all files exist\n315:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n316:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n317:         outputs:\n318:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n319:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n320: \n321:       step_order_dimensions:\n322:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n323:         algorithm: |\n324:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n325:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n326:              correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n327:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n328:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n329:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n330:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n331:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n332:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n333:         outputs:\n334:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n335:           - inventory_pass: true\n336: \n337:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n338:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n339:         outputs:\n340:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n341:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n342:         normalize: |\n343:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n344:             - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n345:             - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n346:             - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n347:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n348: \n349:       step_create_config:\n350:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n351:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n352:         populate:\n353:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n354:           mode: \"review\"\n355:           sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n356:           parentSessionId: null\n357:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n358:           generation: 1\n359:           continuedFromRun: null\n360:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n361:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n362:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n363:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n364:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n365:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n366:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n367:           crossReference:\n368:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n369:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n370:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n371:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n372:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n373:           stuckThreshold: 2\n374:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n375:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n376:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n377:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n378:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n379:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n380:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n381:           status: \"initialized\"\n382:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n383:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n384:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n385: \n386:       step_create_state_log:\n387:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n388:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n389:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n390:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n391:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n392:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n393: \n394:       step_create_findings_registry:\n395:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n396:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n397:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n398: \n399:       step_create_strategy:\n400:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n401:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n402:         populate:\n403:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n404:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n405:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n406:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n407:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n408:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n409:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n410:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n411: \n412:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n413:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n414:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n415:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n416:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n417: \n418:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n419:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n420:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n421:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n422: \n423:       step_init_complete:\n424:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n425:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n426: \n427:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n428:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n429:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n430:   phase_loop:\n431:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n432:     repeat: true\n433:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n434:     steps:\n435: \n436:       step_read_state:\n437:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n438:         read:\n439:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n440:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n441:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n442:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n443:         extract:\n444:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n445:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n446:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n447:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n448:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n449:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n450:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n451:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n452:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n453:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n454:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n455:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n456:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n457:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n458:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n459:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n460:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n461:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n462:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n463:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n464:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n465:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n466:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n467:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n468:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n469: \n470:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n471:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n472:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n473:         if_exists:\n474:           set:\n475:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n476:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n477:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n478:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n479:         if_not_exists:\n480:           proceed: true\n481: \n482:       step_graph_convergence:\n483:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n484:         inspect:\n485:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n486:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n487:         transform: |\n488:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n489:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n490:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n491:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n492:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n493:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n494:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n495:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n496:         outputs:\n497:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n498:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n499:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n500:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n501:           - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n502: \n503:       step_check_convergence:\n504:         action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n505:         algorithm: |\n506:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n507:              claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n508:              If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n509:                candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n510:                stop_blocked = true\n511:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n512:                blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n513:                recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n514:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n515:           1. HARD STOPS:\n516:              a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n517:              b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n518:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n519:           2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n520:              if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n521:           3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n522:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n523:                Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n524:                If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n525:           4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n526:                signals = []\n527:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n528:                   avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n529:                   stop if avg <= 0.08\n530:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n531:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n532:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n533:                c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n534:                   coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n535:                   stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n536:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n537:                if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n538:                if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n539:           5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n540:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n541:                b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n542:                c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n543:                d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n544:                e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n545:                f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n546:                g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n547:                h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n548:                i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n549:              if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n550:                decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n551:                stop_blocked = true\n552:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n553:                blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n554:                blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n555:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n556:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n557:                dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n558:                dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n559:                dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n560:                p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n561:                active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n562:                evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n563:                avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n564:                hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n565:                claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n566:                claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n567:                fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n568:                security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n569:                fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n570:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n571:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n572:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n573:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n574:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n575:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n576:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n577:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n578:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n579:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n580:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n581:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n582:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n583:                     stop_blocked = true\n584:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n585:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n586:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n587:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n588:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n589:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n590:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n591:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n592:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n593:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n594:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n595:                     stop_blocked = false\n596:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n597:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n598:         outputs:\n599:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n600:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n601:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n602:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n603:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n604:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n605:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n606:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n607:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n608:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n609:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n610:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n611:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n612:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n613:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n614:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n615:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n616:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n617:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n618:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n619:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n620:           - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n621:           - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n622:           - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n623:           - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n624:           - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n625:           - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n626:           - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n627:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n628:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n629:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n630:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n631:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n632: \n633:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n634:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n635:         if_blocked:\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-635. Use offset=636 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-review\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-review\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the advisory lock defined by the spec_check_protocol before session classification\"\n        command: \"Open {state_paths.lock_file} with exclusive non-blocking advisory locking semantics; fail closed on contention.\"\n        note: \"macOS/BSD locking here is advisory. Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n          - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n        algorithm: |\n          0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n             claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n             If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n               candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n               recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n               Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n          1. HARD STOPS:\n             a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n             b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n             Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n          2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n             if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n               graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n               Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n               If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n          4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n               signals = []\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n                  stop if avg <= 0.08\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n                  coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n                  stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n               if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n          5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n               a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n               b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n               c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n               d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n               e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n               f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n               g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n               h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n               i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n             if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n               decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n               blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n               convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n               convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n               dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n               dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n               p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n               active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n               evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n               avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n               hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n               fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n               security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n               fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":635,"totalLines":636,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1780906975615,"end":1780906975623}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_026bcb7bde4a4d56016a267bdf83dc8191bc561eb15970c5d4"}},"id":"prt_ea653e17d001LlVuoQHY7i683B","sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","messageID":"msg_ea65391be001soWxilxpMDrfUs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780906975628,"sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_llfkDK8umCD0rvUnoKRMrd6O","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review State Format\n3: description: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Review State Format\n7: \n8: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: The deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n15: \n16: | File | Format | Mutability |\n17: |------|--------|------------|\n18: | `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n19: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n20: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n21: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n22: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n23: | `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n24: | `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n25: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n26: \n27: ```text\n28: {artifact_dir}/\n29:   deep-review-config.json\n30:   deep-review-state.jsonl\n31:   deep-review-findings-registry.json\n32:   deep-review-strategy.md\n33:   deep-review-dashboard.md\n34:   .deep-review-pause\n35:   review-report.md\n36:   iterations/\n37:     iteration-001.md\n38:     iteration-002.md\n39:     ...\n40: ```\n41: \n42: `{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n43: \n44: ### When to Use\n45: \n46: - Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n47: - Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n48: - Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n49: - Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n54: \n55: Created during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n56: \n57: ```json\n58: {\n59:   \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n60:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n61:   \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n62:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n63:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n64:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n65:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n66:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n67:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n68:   \"generation\": 1,\n69:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n70:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n71:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n72:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n73:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n74:   \"crossReference\": {\n75:     \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n76:     \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n77:   },\n78:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n79:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n80:   \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n81:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n82:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n83:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n84:   \"fileProtection\": {\n85:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n86:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n87:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n88:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n89:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n90:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n91:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n92:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n93:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n94:   },\n95:   \"reducer\": {\n96:     \"enabled\": true,\n97:     \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n98:     \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n99:     \"metrics\": [\n100:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n101:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n102:       \"openFindings\",\n103:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n104:       \"convergenceScore\"\n105:     ]\n106:   }\n107: }\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Field Reference\n111: \n112: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n113: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n114: | mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n115: | reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n116: | reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n117: | reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n118: | resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n119: | sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n120: | parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n121: | lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n122: | generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n123: | continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n124: | maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n125: | convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n126: | stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n127: | severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n128: | crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n129: | qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n130: | specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n131: | status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n132: | releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n133: | fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n134: | reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n135: \n136: ### File Protection Levels\n137: \n138: | Level | Meaning |\n139: |-------|---------|\n140: | immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n141: | append-only | New content added at end only |\n142: | mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n143: | write-once | Created once, never modified |\n144: | auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n145: | operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n146: \n147: ### Review Dimensions\n148: \n149: | Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n150: |-----------|----------|---------------------|\n151: | correctness | 1 | Yes |\n152: | security | 2 | Yes |\n153: | traceability | 3 | Yes |\n154: | maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n155: \n156: ### Severity Weights\n157: \n158: | Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n159: |----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n160: | P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n161: | P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n162: | P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 3. STATE LOG\n167: \n168: The `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n173: \n174: Updated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n175: \n176: ### Required Sections\n177: \n178: | Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n179: |---------|-----------|---------|\n180: | topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n181: | review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n182: | completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n183: | running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n184: | what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n185: | what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n186: | exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n187: | ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n188: | next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n189: | known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n190: | cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n191: | files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n192: | review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n193: \n194: ### Mapping from Research Mode\n195: \n196: | Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n197: |---------------|-------------------|\n198: | review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n199: | completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n200: | running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n201: | cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n202: | files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n203: | review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n204: \n205: Sections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n206: \n207: ### Update Protocol\n208: \n209: 1. Read current strategy file\n210: 2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n211: 3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n212: 4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n213: 5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n214: 6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n219: \n220: Reducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n221: \n222: ```json\n223: {\n224:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n225:   \"generation\": 1,\n226:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n227:   \"openFindings\": [],\n228:   \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n229:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n230:   \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n231:   \"severityChanged\": [],\n232:   \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n233:   \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n234:     \"correctness\": true,\n235:     \"security\": true,\n236:     \"traceability\": false,\n237:     \"maintainability\": false\n238:   },\n239:   \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n240:     \"P0\": 0,\n241:     \"P1\": 1,\n242:     \"P2\": 2\n243:   },\n244:   \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n245:   \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n246:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n247:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n248:   \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n249:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n250:   \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: This file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n255: \n256: ### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n257: \n258: | Field | Type | Description |\n259: |-------|------|-------------|\n260: | `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n261: | `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n262: | `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n263: | `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n264: | `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n265: \n266: ### Default Values\n267: \n268: When no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\n269: When no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\n270: When JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n271: \n272: ### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n273: \n274: - **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n275: - **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n276: - **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n277: - **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n282: \n283: Write-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n284: \n285: ### Structure\n286: \n287: ```markdown\n288: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n289: \n290: ## Focus\n291: [Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n292: \n293: ## Scorecard\n294: - Dimensions covered: [list]\n295: - Files reviewed: [count]\n296: - New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n297: - Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n298: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n299: \n300: ## Findings\n301: \n302: ### P0, Blocker\n303: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n304: \n305: ### P1, Required\n306: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n307: \n308: ### P2, Suggestion\n309: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n310: \n311: ## Cross-Reference Results\n312: | Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n313: |----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n314: | spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n315: \n316: ## Assessment\n317: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n318: - Dimensions addressed: [list]\n319: - Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n320: \n321: ## Ruled Out\n322: - [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n323: \n324: ## Dead Ends\n325: - [Direction]: [Why]\n326: \n327: ## Recommended Next Focus\n328: [What to investigate next]\n329: ```\n330: \n331: Every finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n336: \n337: The review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n338: \n339: | # | Section | Description |\n340: |---|---------|-------------|\n341: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n342: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n343: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n344: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n345: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n346: | 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n347: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n348: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n349: | 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n350: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n351: \n352: **Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n353: \n354: **Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n355: \n356: **Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n357: \n358: **Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n359: \n360: **Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n361: \n362: **Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n363: \n364: **Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n365: \n366: **Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n367: \n368: **Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n369: \n370: ---\n371: \n372: ## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n373: \n374: Auto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n375: \n376: - **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n377: - **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n378: - **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n379: - **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n380: \n381: ### Sections\n382: \n383: | Section | Source | Description |\n384: |---------|--------|-------------|\n385: | Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n386: | Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n387: | Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n388: | Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n389: \n390: **Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n395: \n396: Every new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n397: \n398: ### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n399: \n400: Embed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n401: \n402: ```json\n403: {\n404:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n405:   \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n406:   \"evidenceRefs\": [\n407:     \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n408:     \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n409:   ],\n410:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n411:   \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n412:   \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n413:   \"confidence\": 0.86,\n414:   \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n415:   \"transitions\": [\n416:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n417:   ]\n418: }\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ### Required Fields\n422: \n423: | Field | Type | Description |\n424: |-------|------|-------------|\n425: | `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n426: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n427: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n428: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n429: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n430: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n431: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n432: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n433: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n434: \n435: ### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n436: \n437: 1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n438: 2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n439: 3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n440: 4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n441: 5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n442: \n443: ### Severity Transition Rules\n444: \n445: - **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n446: - **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n447: - **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n448: - Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n453: \n454: Each finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n455: \n456: ### Schema\n457: \n458: ```json\n459: {\n460:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n461:   \"severity\": \"P1\",\n462:   \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n463:   \"status\": \"active\",\n464:   \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n465:   \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n466:   \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml\",\n467:   \"line\": 955,\n468:   \"firstSeen\": 2,\n469:   \"lastSeen\": 4,\n470:   \"transitions\": [\n471:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n472:     { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n473:   ]\n474: }\n475: ```\n476: \n477: | Field | Type | Description |\n478: |-------|------|-------------|\n479: | findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n480: | severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n481: | category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n482: | status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n483: | dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n484: | title | string | Short description |\n485: | file | string | File path |\n486: | line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n487: | firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n488: | transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n489: \n490: ### Status Lifecycle\n491: \n492: ```text\n493: [discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n494:                   |\n495:                   +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n496:                   |\n497:                   +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n498: ```\n499: \n500: | Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n501: |--------|----------------------|\n502: | active | Yes |\n503: | resolved | No |\n504: | deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n505: | disproved | No |\n506: \n507: ### Deduplication\n508: \n509: Same file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n510: \n511: ### Cross-Reference Protocols\n512: \n513: | Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n514: |----------|-------|------------|------|\n515: | spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n516: | checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n517: | skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n518: | agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n519: | feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n520: | playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n521: \n522: Severity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n523: - `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n524: - `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n525: - `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n526: \n527: ### Quality Gates\n528: \n529: | Gate | Rule |\n530: |------|------|\n531: | Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n532: | Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n533: | Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n534: \n535: All three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.\n\n(End of file - total 535 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n\n| File | Format | Mutability |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n\n| File | Format | Mutability |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n| `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n| `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n\n```text\n{artifact_dir}/\n  deep-review-config.json\n  deep-review-state.jsonl\n  deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  deep-review-strategy.md\n  deep-review-dashboard.md\n  .deep-review-pause\n  review-report.md\n  iterations/\n    iteration-001.md\n    iteration-002.md\n    ...\n```\n\n`{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n- Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n- Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n- Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n\nCreated during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n    \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n    \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Field Reference\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n| reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n| reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n| reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n| resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n| sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n| parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n| lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n| generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n| continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n| maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n| convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n| stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n| qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n| specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n| status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n| releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n| fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n| reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n\n### File Protection Levels\n\n| Level | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n| append-only | New content added at end only |\n| mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n| write-once | Created once, never modified |\n| auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n| operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|---------------------|\n| correctness | 1 | Yes |\n| security | 2 | Yes |\n| traceability | 3 | Yes |\n| maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n| P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n| P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n| P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## 3. STATE LOG\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n\nUpdated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n\n### Required Sections\n\n| Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n| review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n| completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n| running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n| what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n| what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n| exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n| ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n| next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n| known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n| cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n| files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n| review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n\n### Mapping from Research Mode\n\n| Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n|---------------|-------------------|\n| review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n| completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n| running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n\nSections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n\n### Update Protocol\n\n1. Read current strategy file\n2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n\nReducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"openFindings\": [],\n  \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n  \"severityChanged\": [],\n  \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n  \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n    \"correctness\": true,\n    \"security\": true,\n    \"traceability\": false,\n    \"maintainability\": false\n  },\n  \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n    \"P0\": 0,\n    \"P1\": 1,\n    \"P2\": 2\n  },\n  \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n  \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n  \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n}\n```\n\nThis file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n\n### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n| `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n| `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n| `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n| `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n\n### Default Values\n\nWhen no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\nWhen no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\nWhen JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n\n### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n\n- **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n- **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n- **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n- **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n\nWrite-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n\n### Structure\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: [list]\n- Files reviewed: [count]\n- New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P1, Required\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Dimensions addressed: [list]\n- Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n\n## Ruled Out\n- [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n\n## Dead Ends\n- [Direction]: [Why]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next]\n```\n\nEvery finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n\nThe review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n\n| # | Section | Description |\n|---|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n\n**Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n\n**Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n\n**Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n\n**Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n\n**Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n\n**Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n\n**Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n\n**Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n\n**Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n\n---\n\n## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n\nAuto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n\n- **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n- **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n- **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n\n### Sections\n\n| Section | Source | Description |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n| Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n| Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n| Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n\n**Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n\n---\n\n## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n\n### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n\nEmbed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n    \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Required Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n\n1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n\n### Severity Transition Rules\n\n- **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n- **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n- **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n- Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n\n---\n\n## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n\nEach finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n\n### Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"severity\": \"P1\",\n  \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n  \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n  \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml\",\n  \"line\": 955,\n  \"firstSeen\": 2,\n  \"lastSeen\": 4,\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n    { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n| severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n| category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n| status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n| dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n| title | string | Short description |\n| file | string | File path |\n| line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n| firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n| transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n\n### Status Lifecycle\n\n```text\n[discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n                  |\n                  +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n                  |\n                  +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n```\n\n| Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| active | Yes |\n| resolved | No |\n| deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n| disproved | No |\n\n### Deduplication\n\nSame file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n\n### Cross-Reference Protocols\n\n| Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n|----------|-------|------------|------|\n| spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n| checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n| skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n| agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n| feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n| playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n\nSeverity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n- `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n- `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n- `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n\n### Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n| Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n| Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n\nAll three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":535,"totalLines":535,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1780906975608,"end":1780906975626}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_026bcb7bde4a4d56016a267bdf83c481919e48729eb3f9f84a"}},"id":"prt_ea653e176001w0bqb7xNG7H4Fm","sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","messageID":"msg_ea65391be001soWxilxpMDrfUs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780906975629,"sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oQXDRx76ZVKVtis1cUFVW7Xs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: ---\n10: \n11: # Deep Review State Outputs\n12: \n13: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n24: \n25: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n26: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n27: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n28: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n29: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n30: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n31: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n32: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n33: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n34: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n39: \n40: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n41: \n42: ```text\n43: Review verdict: PASS\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ```text\n47: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ```text\n51: Review verdict: FAIL\n52: ```\n53: \n54: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n59: \n60: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n61: \n62: - Current iteration and next focus.\n63: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n64: - Dimension coverage.\n65: - Convergence trend.\n66: - Gate blockers.\n67: - Provisional verdict.\n68: \n69: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n74: \n75: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n76: \n77: - Executive summary.\n78: - Planning trigger.\n79: - Active finding registry.\n80: - Remediation workstreams.\n81: - Spec seed.\n82: - Plan seed.\n83: - Traceability status.\n84: - Deferred items.\n85: - Audit appendix.\n86: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n91: \n92: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n93: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n94: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":94,"totalLines":94,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1780906975612,"end":1780906975628}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_026bcb7bde4a4d56016a267bdf83d08191ba05709115dddd42"}},"id":"prt_ea653e179001yUwvoFTI5HlScm","sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","messageID":"msg_ea65391be001soWxilxpMDrfUs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780906975638,"sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_akPfRwlR9wtK9TsyTCs1upDB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\n7: \n8: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: ### Purpose\n15: \n16: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n17: \n18: ### When to Use\n19: \n20: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n21: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n22: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n23: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n24: \n25: ```\n26: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n27: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n28: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n29: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n30: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n31: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n32: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n33: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n34: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n35: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n36: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n37: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n38: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n39: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n40: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n41: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n42: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### Core Innovation\n46: \n47: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n48: \n49: ### Key References\n50: \n51: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n52: |----------|------|---------|\n53: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n54: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n55: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n56: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n57: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n62: \n63: ### Purpose\n64: \n65: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n66: \n67: ### Steps\n68: \n69: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n70:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n71:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n72:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n73:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n74: \n75: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n76: \n77: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n78: \n79:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n80:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n81:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n82:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n83:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n84:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n85:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n86: \n87:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n88: \n89: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n90: \n91:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n92:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\n93:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n94:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n95:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n96:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n97: \n98:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n99: \n100: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n101: \n102:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n103:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n104:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n105:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n106:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n107:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n108:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n109:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n110: \n111:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n112: \n113: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n114: \n115: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n116: \n117: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n118: \n119: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n120:    - Topic (review target description)\n121:    - Review Dimensions checklist\n122:    - Files Under Review table\n123:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n124:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n125:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n126:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n127:    - Review Boundaries from config\n128: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n129:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n130:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n131: \n132: 10. **Validate review charter**:\n133:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n134:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n135:    - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n136: \n137: 11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n138: \n139: ### Outputs\n140: \n141: | File | Location | Purpose |\n142: |------|----------|---------|\n143: | Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n144: | State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n145: | Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n146: | Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n151: \n152: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n153: \n154: #### Step 1: Read State\n155: \n156: - Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n157: - Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n158: - Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n159: \n160: Reducer contract for every loop refresh:\n161: \n162: | Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n163: |--------------|-----------------|-------|\n164: | Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n165: | Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n166: | Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n167: \n168: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n169: \n170: Run `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n171: \n172: - Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n173: - Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n174: - Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n175:   - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n176:   - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n177:   - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n178:   - Required traceability protocols are covered\n179:   - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n180: - Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n181: \n182: If convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n183: \n184: - `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n185: - `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n186: - `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n187: \n188: The blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n189: \n190: Convergence signals and weights:\n191: \n192: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n193: |--------|--------|-------------|\n194: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n195: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n196: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n197: \n198: **P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n199: \n200: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n201: \n202: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n203: \n204: 1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n205: 2. If present:\n206:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n207:    - Halt the loop with message:\n208:      ```\n209:      Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n210:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n211:      ```\n212:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n213: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n214:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n215:    - Continue from step_read_state\n216: \n217: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n218: \n219: Normalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n220: \n221: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n222: \n223: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n224: \n225: ```\n226: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\n227: Iteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\n228: Target: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\n229: Dimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\n230: Findings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\n231: Traceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\n232: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n233: Provisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\n234: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n235: ```\n236: \n237: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n238: \n239: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n240: \n241: Dispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n242: \n243: ```\n244: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n245: \n246: Review Target: {config.reviewTarget}\n247: Review Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\n248: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n249: Focus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\n250: Focus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\n251: Remaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\n252: Traceability Protocols:\n253:   - Core: {core_protocols}\n254:   - Overlay: {overlay_protocols}\n255: Active Findings: {findingsSummary}\n256: State Files:\n257:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\n258:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\n259:   - Registry: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\n260:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\n261: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n262: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n263: CONSTRAINT: Target files are READ-ONLY -- never modify code under review\n264: ```\n265: \n266: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n267: \n268: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n269: \n270: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-review` agent with model Opus.\n271: - `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n272: - `cli-gemini` (spec 019): positional prompt to `gemini \"$(cat prompt)\" -m X -s none -y -o text`. Model whitelist enforced (`gemini-3.1-pro-preview` only). No reasoning-effort or service-tier flags.\n273: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only). We override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n274: \n275: All branches share:\n276: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n277: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n278: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n279: \n280: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n281: \n282: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope. See the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n283: \n284: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n285: \n286: **Agent constraints**:\n287: - `@deep-review` is LEAF-only: it cannot dispatch sub-agents\n288: - No WebFetch: review is code-only and read-only\n289: - Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle\n290: - Tools available: Read, Grep, Glob, Edit (state files only), code_graph_query + Grep\n291: \n292: #### Step 3a: Cross-Reference Protocol Execution\n293: \n294: During iterations focused on the Traceability dimension, the agent executes applicable cross-reference protocols. Each protocol produces a structured result appended to the JSONL `traceabilityChecks.results[]` array.\n295: \n296: | Protocol | Execution | Expected Output |\n297: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n298: | `spec_code` | Compare normative claims in spec.md against shipped implementation | Pass/partial/fail per claim with file:line evidence |\n299: | `checklist_evidence` | Verify every `[x]` mark in checklist.md has supporting evidence | Pass/partial/fail per checked item |\n300: | `skill_agent` | Compare SKILL.md contracts against runtime agent definitions | Agreement/drift/disagreement per capability |\n301: | `agent_cross_runtime` | Compare agent definitions across runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .codex) | Parity/drift/divergence per runtime pair |\n302: | `feature_catalog_code` | Compare catalog claims against discoverable implementation | Match/stale/missing per feature |\n303: | `playbook_capability` | Validate playbook scenarios against executable reality | Executable/needs-update/impossible per scenario |\n304: \n305: Each protocol result includes:\n306: - `protocolId`: Protocol identifier\n307: - `status`: `pass`, `partial`, or `fail`\n308: - `gateClass`: `hard` or `advisory`\n309: - `applicable`: Whether the protocol applies to this target type\n310: - `counts`: `{ pass, partial, fail, skipped }`\n311: - `evidence`: Array of file:line citations\n312: - `findingRefs`: Array of finding IDs generated from this protocol\n313: - `summary`: Human-readable summary text\n314: \n315: #### Step 3b: Resource Map Coverage Audit\n316: \n317: When `config.resource_map_present == true`, at least one loop iteration MUST audit implementation-vs-resource-map coverage:\n318: \n319: 1. Read `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`\n320: 2. Read applied reports under `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md`\n321: 3. Cross-check `target_files` from the applied reports against resource-map entries\n322: 4. Classify outcomes into:\n323:    - entries touched\n324:    - entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`)\n325:    - implementation paths absent from the map\n326: 5. Emit any resulting findings with category `resource-map-coverage`\n327: \n328: When `config.resource_map_present == false`, skip this audit and rely on the `Known Context` note: `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate`.\n329: \n330: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n331: \n332: After agent completes:\n333: \n334: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n335: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with review iteration fields:\n336:    - `dimensions` (array of dimensions covered)\n337:    - `filesReviewed` (array of file paths)\n338:    - `findingsSummary` (cumulative P0/P1/P2 counts)\n339:    - `findingsNew` (this iteration's new findings)\n340:    - `traceabilityChecks` (protocol results if applicable)\n341: 3. Verify strategy.md was updated (dimension progress, findings count, protocol status)\n342: 4. Extract `newFindingsRatio` from JSONL record\n343: 5. Update stuck tracking using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`:\n344:    - Skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change)\n345:    - Reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress)\n346:    - Increment if `newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold`\n347:    - Reset otherwise\n348: \n349: #### Step 4a: Claim Adjudication\n350: \n351: Before the next convergence pass, the orchestrator adjudicates every new P0/P1 finding with a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. This step prevents false positives from inflating severity and distorting convergence, AND acts as a hard STOP gate: `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` appends a `claim_adjudication` event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree consults that event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`). A missing or failing packet vetoes STOP even when every other gate passes.\n352: \n353: Each new P0/P1 must carry a typed packet with the following required fields (see `../state/state_format.md` §9 for the full schema and a worked example):\n354: \n355: | Field | Type | Description |\n356: |-------|------|-------------|\n357: | `findingId` | string | Matches the finding ID in the iteration body |\n358: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes |\n359: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations (≥ 1) |\n360: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the orchestrator looked for contradicting evidence |\n361: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative explanation, even if rejected |\n362: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication |\n363: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Orchestrator confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n364: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | Concrete condition that would cause a future downgrade |\n365: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n366: \n367: **Protocol**:\n368: \n369: 1. Re-read the cited evidence at the referenced file:line locations.\n370: 2. Seek counterevidence in adjacent code, docs, or prior iteration history.\n371: 3. Record an alternative explanation even if it is rejected.\n372: 4. Confirm or downgrade severity before the finding becomes convergence-visible.\n373: 5. Emit the typed packet inside the iteration file so `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` can parse it.\n374: \n375: **Failure semantics**: when any new P0/P1 finding is missing a packet or a required field, the workflow records `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. On the next loop, `step_check_convergence` step 0 (universal pre-check) routes STOP to `BLOCKED` with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet. Downgraded findings have their `finalSeverity` updated. The original severity is preserved in the iteration file for audit trail.\n376: \n377: #### Step 4b: Generate Dashboard\n378: \n379: Generate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` with review-specific sections:\n380: \n381: | Section | Content |\n382: |---------|---------|\n383: | Status | Provisional verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`/`PENDING`) and `hasAdvisories` flag |\n384: | Findings Summary | P0/P1/P2 counts with deltas from previous iteration |\n385: | Progress Table | Iteration number, focus dimension, `newFindingsRatio`, findings count, status |\n386: | Coverage | Files reviewed, dimensions completed, traceability protocol status |\n387: | Trend | Last 3 `newFindingsRatio` values with direction indicator (ascending/descending/flat) |\n388: | Active Risks | Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings |\n389: \n390: Dashboard behavior:\n391: - Auto-generated only -- never manually edited\n392: - Overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n393: - Non-blocking: if generation fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n394: - In **confirm mode**: displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate\n395: - In **auto mode**: written silently for post-hoc review\n396: \n397: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n398: \n399: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n400: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: apply review-specific recovery strategies (see Section 3a), reset stuck count, continue\n401: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n402: \n403: ### Stuck Recovery (Review-Specific)\n404: \n405: **Threshold:** 2 consecutive no-progress iterations (`noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n406: \n407: | Failure Mode | Detection | Recovery Strategy |\n408: |-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n409: | Same dimension stuck | Last 2 iterations reviewed the same dimension with ratios `< 0.05` | **Change granularity**: if reviewing at file level, zoom into functions, if reviewing functions, zoom out to module level |\n410: | Traceability plateau | Required protocols remain partial while ratios stay `< 0.05` | **Protocol-first replay**: re-run the unresolved traceability protocol directly against the conflicting artifacts |\n411: | Low-value advisory churn | Last 2 iterations found only P2 work | **Escalate severity review**: explicitly search for P0/P1 patterns or downgrade unsupported severity claims |\n412: \n413: **Selection logic**:\n414: \n415: ```\n416: function selectReviewRecoveryStrategy(stuckIterations, state, config):\n417:   lastFocuses = [i.focus for i in stuckIterations[-2:]]\n418: \n419:   // Same dimension stuck? Change granularity\n420:   if len(set(lastFocuses)) <= 1:\n421:     return { strategy: \"change_granularity\", dimension: lastFocuses[0] }\n422: \n423:   // Required protocol plateau?\n424:   if hasRequiredProtocolPlateau(state.traceabilityChecks):\n425:     return { strategy: \"protocol_first_replay\" }\n426: \n427:   // Default: escalate severity\n428:   return { strategy: \"escalate_severity_review\" }\n429: ```\n430: \n431: **Recovery evaluation**:\n432: - If recovery iteration finds any new P0/P1 or materially advances required traceability coverage: recovery successful. Reset stuck count. Continue.\n433: - If recovery iteration finds only P2 or nothing: recovery failed. If all dimensions are already covered, exit to synthesis. Otherwise, move to the next unreviewed dimension.\n434: \n435: ---\n436: \n437: ## 4. PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n438: \n439: ### Purpose\n440: \n441: Compile all iteration findings into the final `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`. The synthesis phase owns the canonical review report output.\n442: \n443: ### Steps\n444: \n445: #### Step 1: Finding Registry Deduplication\n446: \n447: Consolidate findings across all iterations:\n448: \n449: 1. Read all iteration files: `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n450: 2. Group findings by file + line range + root cause\n451: 3. Merge duplicates, keeping the highest severity and all evidence\n452: 4. Assign final finding IDs: `F001`, `F002`, ...\n453: 5. Preserve the audit trail: note which iterations contributed to each merged finding\n454: \n455: #### Step 2: Severity Reconciliation\n456: \n457: Use adjudicated `finalSeverity` for any P0/P1 that was downgraded during claim adjudication (Step 4a of the iteration loop). The original severity from the iteration file is preserved in the audit appendix.\n458: \n459: #### Step 3: Replay Validation\n460: \n461: Recompute the convergence outcome from JSONL state before finalizing the report:\n462: \n463: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` and select review-mode iteration records in run order\n464: 2. Recompute `newFindingsRatio`, rolling-average votes, MAD votes, and coverage votes from stored JSONL fields only\n465: 3. Recompute `traceabilityChecks.summary` and confirm required protocol statuses match the recorded coverage vote\n466: 4. Re-run the evidence, scope, and coverage gates against stored findings and scope data\n467: 5. Compare the replayed decision and stop reason to the recorded synthesis event\n468: \n469: This synthesis-stage replay is a **full-history audit replay** over the stored JSONL state. It follows the same full-history replay discipline as the per-iteration reducer refresh above, but runs as an explicit pre-synthesis audit.\n470: \n471: Replay passes only when the recomputed decision, thresholds, and gate outcomes agree with the persisted result. If replay fails, log a warning in the audit appendix but proceed with synthesis.\n472: \n473: #### Step 4: Compile review-report.md\n474: \n475: Generate the 9 core review-report sections (defined in `review_mode_contract.yaml` under `outputs.reviewReport`) and insert `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` between `Traceability Status` and `Deferred Items` when `config.resource_map_present == true`:\n476: \n477: | # | Section | Purpose |\n478: |---|---------|---------|\n479: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` metadata |\n480: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n481: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduplicated active findings with evidence and final severity |\n482: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n483: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n484: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n485: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n486: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `config.resource_map_present == true`, reports touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n487: | 9 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n488: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, convergence evidence |\n489: \n490: #### Step 5: Verdict Determination\n491: \n492: Apply the verdict contract from `review_mode_contract.yaml`:\n493: \n494: | Verdict | Condition | Next Command |\n495: |---------|-----------|--------------|\n496: | **FAIL** | Active P0 remains OR any required binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n497: | **CONDITIONAL** | No active P0, but active P1 remains | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n498: | **PASS** | No active P0/P1 | `/create:changelog` |\n499: \n500: When `PASS` verdict is issued and active P2 findings remain, set `hasAdvisories = true` in the report metadata.\n501: \n502: #### Step 6: Finalize State\n503: \n504: 1. Update config status: Set `status: \"complete\"` in `deep-review-config.json`\n505: 2. Write final JSONL entry:\n506:    ```json\n507:    {\n508:      \"type\": \"event\",\n509:      \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n510:      \"mode\": \"review\",\n511:      \"totalIterations\": N,\n512:      \"verdict\": \"PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\",\n513:      \"activeP0\": N,\n514:      \"activeP1\": N,\n515:      \"activeP2\": N,\n516:      \"dimensionCoverage\": X,\n517:      \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n518:      \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n519:    }\n520:    ```\n521: \n522: ---\n523: \n524: ## 5. PHASE 4: SAVE\n525: \n526: ### Purpose\n527: \n528: Preserve review context to the memory system for future session recovery and cross-session continuity.\n529: \n530: ### Steps\n531: \n532: 1. **Generate context**: Run the memory save script with the spec folder:\n533:    ```bash\n534:    node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}\n535:    ```\n536: \n537: 2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow.\n538: \n539: 3. **Verify**: Confirm `memory/*.md` file was created with proper anchors.\n540: \n541: ### On Save Failure\n542: \n543: If memory save fails:\n544: - Preserve the current `review/` packet as backup (the disk state is the ground truth)\n545: - Log the error\n546: - The review results remain intact in `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` regardless of memory save status\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ## 6. AUTO-RESUME PROTOCOL\n551: \n552: ### Purpose\n553: \n554: Enable review sessions to resume cleanly from prior state when interrupted by context compaction, process termination, or intentional pause.\n555: \n556: ### Resume Detection\n557: \n558: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n559: \n560: 1. **Verify agreement**: Confirm config, JSONL, findings registry, and strategy all exist and agree on target/spec folder\n561: 2. **Count progress**: Read JSONL, count iteration records, determine last completed iteration\n562: 3. **Read strategy**: Load current dimension progress, findings, and next focus from `deep-review-strategy.md`\n563: 4. **Set counter**: Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n564: 5. **Log resume**: Append the canonical resume event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The reducer requires every field below:\n565:    ```json\n566:    {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-24T14:05:00Z\"}\n567:    ```\n568: 6. **Continue**: Enter the iteration loop from step_read_state\n569: \n570: ### Lifecycle Branches (current release)\n571: \n572: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures. Until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n573: \n574: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n575: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n576: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n577: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n578: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `review/` tree moved under `review_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus non-null `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n579: \n580: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n581: \n582: ```json\n583: {\n584:   \"type\": \"event\",\n585:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n586:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n587:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n588:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n589:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n590:   \"generation\": <number>,\n591:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n592:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n593:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n594: }\n595: ```\n596: \n597: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n598: \n599: ### State Validation on Resume\n600: \n601: | Condition | Classification | Action |\n602: |-----------|---------------|--------|\n603: | Config + JSONL + strategy all exist and agree | `resume` | Continue from last iteration + 1 |\n604: | All exist, config says `status: \"complete\"` | `completed-session` | Report completion, ask user if re-review desired |\n605: | Partial files or contradictions | `invalid-state` | Halt for repair, do not guess |\n606: | No files exist | `fresh` | Start new initialization |\n607: \n608: ### State Recovery Cascade\n609: \n610: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this priority cascade:\n611: \n612: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n613: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n614: | 1 | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation |\n615: | 2 | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract dimensions, findings, coverage |\n616: | 3 | JSONL missing, iteration files exist | Scan `review/iterations/iteration-*.md`, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n617: | 4 | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase |\n618: | 5 | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n619: \n620: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next.\n621: \n622: ---\n623: \n624: ## 7. PAUSE/RESUME\n625: \n626: ### Pause Sentinel Behavior\n627: \n628: The pause sentinel provides graceful loop suspension in autonomous mode without killing the process.\n629: \n630: ### Creating a Pause\n631: \n632: Create the sentinel file at any time:\n633: \n634: ```bash\n635: touch {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n636: ```\n637: \n638: The orchestrator checks for this file between iterations (Step 2a). When detected:\n639: - The current iteration is allowed to complete\n640: - The loop halts before dispatching the next iteration\n641: - A paused event is logged to JSONL\n642: - The user is notified with current state (iteration count, dimensions covered, findings)\n643: \n644: ### Resuming After Pause\n645: \n646: Delete the sentinel file and restart the workflow:\n647: \n648: ```bash\n649: rm {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n650: ```\n651: \n652: On the next invocation:\n653: - The auto-resume protocol (Section 6) detects the existing state\n654: - A resumed event is logged to JSONL\n655: - The loop continues from the next iteration\n656: \n657: ### Confirm Mode Approval Gates\n658: \n659: In confirm mode (`deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml`), the workflow adds explicit approval gates instead of relying on the pause sentinel:\n660: \n661: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n662: |---------------|----------|\n663: | After initialization | Show config, strategy, and scope. Wait for approval |\n664: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings, dashboard, and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n665: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n666: | After synthesis | Show final review-report.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS, ERROR HANDLING, AND QUALITY GATES\n671: \n672: State-transition rules, error handling, and the review quality gates live in `loop_state_and_gates.md` for navigability.\n673: \n674: ---\n675: \n676: ## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n677: \n678: ### Shared Protocol Documentation\n679: \n680: Protocol documents from `deep-research` are cross-referenced, not duplicated:\n681: \n682: | Document | Path | Purpose |\n683: |----------|------|---------|\n684: | Loop Protocol (research) | `../deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` | Research loop lifecycle (this file adapts Section 9) |\n685: | State Format | `../deep-research/references/state/state_format.md` | JSONL, strategy, and config schemas |\n686: | Convergence | `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` | `shouldContinue_review()` (Section 10), stuck recovery, quality guards |\n687: \n688: ### Review-Specific Resources\n689: \n690: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n691: |----------|------|---------|\n692: | Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n693: | Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n694: | Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n695: | Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n696: | Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n697: \n698: ### Workflow Files\n699: \n700: | Mode | Path |\n701: |------|------|\n702: | Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` |\n703: | Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` |\n704: \n705: ### Agent\n706: \n707: | Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n708: |-------|-------------|------------|\n709: | `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n710: \n711: Runtime paths:\n712: - OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n713: - Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n714: - Codex: `.codex/agents/deep-review.toml`\n715: \n716: ---\n717: \n718: ## Executor Selection Contract\n719: \n720: Executor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n721: \n722: ### Invariants\n723: \n724: Every executor path MUST satisfy:\n725: \n726: 1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n727: 2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n728: 3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n729: \n730: ### Failure Modes\n731: \n732: - Missing iteration file: `iteration_file_missing` from `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event.\n733: - Empty iteration file: `iteration_file_empty`, same downstream.\n734: - JSONL not appended: `jsonl_not_appended`.\n735: - JSONL missing required fields: `jsonl_missing_fields`.\n736: - JSONL malformed: `jsonl_parse_error`.\n737: - 3 consecutive failures: existing `stuck_recovery` event (unchanged).\n738: \n739: ### JSONL Audit Field\n740: \n741: Non-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n742: \n743: ### Template And Config Surface\n744: \n745: The executor-agnostic iteration prompt lives at `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, rendered by `prompt-pack.ts` before dispatch and either injected as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\n746: \n747: ### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\n748: \n749: - YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\n750: - `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\n751: - Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\n752: - The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\n753: \n754: ### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n755: \n756: On this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\n\n(End of file - total 756 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n- Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n- Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n- Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n│              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n│ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n│ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n│ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n│ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n│ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n│              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n└──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Innovation\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Key References\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n| Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n| Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\n\nSet up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n\n2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n\n3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n\n   | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n   |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n   | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n   | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n   | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n   | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n   | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n\n   Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n\n4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n\n   | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n   |----------|-----------|-----------|\n   | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n   | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n   | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n   | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n\n   Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n\n5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n\n   | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n   |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n   | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n   | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n   | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n   | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n   | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n   | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n\n   Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n\n6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n\n7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n\n8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n\n9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n   - Topic (review target description)\n   - Review Dimensions checklist\n   - Files Under Review table\n   - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n   - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n   - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n   - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n   - Review Boundaries from config\n9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n   - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n\n10. **Validate review charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n\n11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n\n### Outputs\n\n| File | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n| State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n| Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n| Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n\n- Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n- Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n- Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n\nReducer contract for every loop refresh:\n\n| Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n|--------------|-----------------|-------|\n| Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n| Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n| Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\n\nRun `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n\n- Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n- Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n- Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n  - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n  - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n  - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n  - Required traceability protocols are covered\n  - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n- Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n\nIf convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n- `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n- `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n\nThe blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n\nConvergence signals and weights:\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n\n**P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```\n     Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n\nNormalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\nIteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\nTarget: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\nDimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\nFindings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\nTraceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nProvisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n\nDispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n\n```\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nReview Target: {config.reviewTarget}\nReview Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\nFocus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\nRemaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\nTraceability Protocols:\n  - Core: {core_protocols}\n  - Overlay: {overlay_protocols}\nActive Findings: {findingsSummary}\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\n  - Registry: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\nCONSTRAINT: Target files are READ-ONLY -- never modify code under review\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-review` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n- `cli-gemini` (spec 019): positional prompt to `gemini \"$(cat prompt)\" -m X -s none -y -o text`. Model whitelist enforced (`gemini-3.1-pro-preview` only). No reasoning-effort or service-tier flags.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only). We override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope. See the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\n**Agent constraints**:\n- `@deep-review` is LEAF-only: it cannot dispatch sub-agents\n- No WebFetch: review is code-only and read-only\n- Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle\n- Tools available: Read, Grep, Glob, Edit (state files only), code_graph_query + Grep\n\n#### Step 3a: Cross-Reference Protocol Execution\n\nDuring iterations focused on the Traceability dimension, the agent executes applicable cross-reference protocols. Each protocol produces a structured result appended to the JSONL `traceabilityChecks.results[]` array.\n\n| Protocol | Execution | Expected Output |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| `spec_code` | Compare normative claims in spec.md against shipped implementation | Pass/partial/fail per claim with file:line evidence |\n| `checklist_evidence` | Verify every `[x]` mark in checklist.md has supporting evidence | Pass/partial/fail per checked item |\n| `skill_agent` | Compare SKILL.md contracts against runtime agent definitions | Agreement/drift/disagreement per capability |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | Compare agent definitions across runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .codex) | Parity/drift/divergence per runtime pair |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | Compare catalog claims against discoverable implementation | Match/stale/missing per feature |\n| `playbook_capability` | Validate playbook scenarios against executable reality | Executable/needs-update/impossible per scenario |\n\nEach protocol result includes:\n- `protocolId`: Protocol identifier\n- `status`: `pass`, `partial`, or `fail`\n- `gateClass`: `hard` or `advisory`\n- `applicable`: Whether the protocol applies to this target type\n- `counts`: `{ pass, partial, fail, skipped }`\n- `evidence`: Array of file:line citations\n- `findingRefs`: Array of finding IDs generated from this protocol\n- `summary`: Human-readable summary text\n\n#### Step 3b: Resource Map Coverage Audit\n\nWhen `config.resource_map_present == true`, at least one loop iteration MUST audit implementation-vs-resource-map coverage:\n\n1. Read `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`\n2. Read applied reports under `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md`\n3. Cross-check `target_files` from the applied reports against resource-map entries\n4. Classify outcomes into:\n   - entries touched\n   - entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`)\n   - implementation paths absent from the map\n5. Emit any resulting findings with category `resource-map-coverage`\n\nWhen `config.resource_map_present == false`, skip this audit and rely on the `Known Context` note: `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate`.\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n\nAfter agent completes:\n\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with review iteration fields:\n   - `dimensions` (array of dimensions covered)\n   - `filesReviewed` (array of file paths)\n   - `findingsSummary` (cumulative P0/P1/P2 counts)\n   - `findingsNew` (this iteration's new findings)\n   - `traceabilityChecks` (protocol results if applicable)\n3. Verify strategy.md was updated (dimension progress, findings count, protocol status)\n4. Extract `newFindingsRatio` from JSONL record\n5. Update stuck tracking using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`:\n   - Skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change)\n   - Reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress)\n   - Increment if `newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold`\n   - Reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Claim Adjudication\n\nBefore the next convergence pass, the orchestrator adjudicates every new P0/P1 finding with a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. This step prevents false positives from inflating severity and distorting convergence, AND acts as a hard STOP gate: `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` appends a `claim_adjudication` event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree consults that event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`). A missing or failing packet vetoes STOP even when every other gate passes.\n\nEach new P0/P1 must carry a typed packet with the following required fields (see `../state/state_format.md` §9 for the full schema and a worked example):\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Matches the finding ID in the iteration body |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations (≥ 1) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the orchestrator looked for contradicting evidence |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative explanation, even if rejected |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Orchestrator confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | Concrete condition that would cause a future downgrade |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n**Protocol**:\n\n1. Re-read the cited evidence at the referenced file:line locations.\n2. Seek counterevidence in adjacent code, docs, or prior iteration history.\n3. Record an alternative explanation even if it is rejected.\n4. Confirm or downgrade severity before the finding becomes convergence-visible.\n5. Emit the typed packet inside the iteration file so `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` can parse it.\n\n**Failure semantics**: when any new P0/P1 finding is missing a packet or a required field, the workflow records `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. On the next loop, `step_check_convergence` step 0 (universal pre-check) routes STOP to `BLOCKED` with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet. Downgraded findings have their `finalSeverity` updated. The original severity is preserved in the iteration file for audit trail.\n\n#### Step 4b: Generate Dashboard\n\nGenerate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` with review-specific sections:\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| Status | Provisional verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`/`PENDING`) and `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| Findings Summary | P0/P1/P2 counts with deltas from previous iteration |\n| Progress Table | Iteration number, focus dimension, `newFindingsRatio`, findings count, status |\n| Coverage | Files reviewed, dimensions completed, traceability protocol status |\n| Trend | Last 3 `newFindingsRatio` values with direction indicator (ascending/descending/flat) |\n| Active Risks | Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings |\n\nDashboard behavior:\n- Auto-generated only -- never manually edited\n- Overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n- Non-blocking: if generation fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n- In **confirm mode**: displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate\n- In **auto mode**: written silently for post-hoc review\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: apply review-specific recovery strategies (see Section 3a), reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Stuck Recovery (Review-Specific)\n\n**Threshold:** 2 consecutive no-progress iterations (`noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n| Failure Mode | Detection | Recovery Strategy |\n|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| Same dimension stuck | Last 2 iterations reviewed the same dimension with ratios `< 0.05` | **Change granularity**: if reviewing at file level, zoom into functions, if reviewing functions, zoom out to module level |\n| Traceability plateau | Required protocols remain partial while ratios stay `< 0.05` | **Protocol-first replay**: re-run the unresolved traceability protocol directly against the conflicting artifacts |\n| Low-value advisory churn | Last 2 iterations found only P2 work | **Escalate severity review**: explicitly search for P0/P1 patterns or downgrade unsupported severity claims |\n\n**Selection logic**:\n\n```\nfunction selectReviewRecoveryStrategy(stuckIterations, state, config):\n  lastFocuses = [i.focus for i in stuckIterations[-2:]]\n\n  // Same dimension stuck? Change granularity\n  if len(set(lastFocuses)) <= 1:\n    return { strategy: \"change_granularity\", dimension: lastFocuses[0] }\n\n  // Required protocol plateau?\n  if hasRequiredProtocolPlateau(state.traceabilityChecks):\n    return { strategy: \"protocol_first_replay\" }\n\n  // Default: escalate severity\n  return { strategy: \"escalate_severity_review\" }\n```\n\n**Recovery evaluation**:\n- If recovery iteration finds any new P0/P1 or materially advances required traceability coverage: recovery successful. Reset stuck count. Continue.\n- If recovery iteration finds only P2 or nothing: recovery failed. If all dimensions are already covered, exit to synthesis. Otherwise, move to the next unreviewed dimension.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\n\nCompile all iteration findings into the final `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`. The synthesis phase owns the canonical review report output.\n\n### Steps\n\n#### Step 1: Finding Registry Deduplication\n\nConsolidate findings across all iterations:\n\n1. Read all iteration files: `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. Group findings by file + line range + root cause\n3. Merge duplicates, keeping the highest severity and all evidence\n4. Assign final finding IDs: `F001`, `F002`, ...\n5. Preserve the audit trail: note which iterations contributed to each merged finding\n\n#### Step 2: Severity Reconciliation\n\nUse adjudicated `finalSeverity` for any P0/P1 that was downgraded during claim adjudication (Step 4a of the iteration loop). The original severity from the iteration file is preserved in the audit appendix.\n\n#### Step 3: Replay Validation\n\nRecompute the convergence outcome from JSONL state before finalizing the report:\n\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` and select review-mode iteration records in run order\n2. Recompute `newFindingsRatio`, rolling-average votes, MAD votes, and coverage votes from stored JSONL fields only\n3. Recompute `traceabilityChecks.summary` and confirm required protocol statuses match the recorded coverage vote\n4. Re-run the evidence, scope, and coverage gates against stored findings and scope data\n5. Compare the replayed decision and stop reason to the recorded synthesis event\n\nThis synthesis-stage replay is a **full-history audit replay** over the stored JSONL state. It follows the same full-history replay discipline as the per-iteration reducer refresh above, but runs as an explicit pre-synthesis audit.\n\nReplay passes only when the recomputed decision, thresholds, and gate outcomes agree with the persisted result. If replay fails, log a warning in the audit appendix but proceed with synthesis.\n\n#### Step 4: Compile review-report.md\n\nGenerate the 9 core review-report sections (defined in `review_mode_contract.yaml` under `outputs.reviewReport`) and insert `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` between `Traceability Status` and `Deferred Items` when `config.resource_map_present == true`:\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` metadata |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduplicated active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `config.resource_map_present == true`, reports touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, convergence evidence |\n\n#### Step 5: Verdict Determination\n\nApply the verdict contract from `review_mode_contract.yaml`:\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|--------------|\n| **FAIL** | Active P0 remains OR any required binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | No active P0, but active P1 remains | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| **PASS** | No active P0/P1 | `/create:changelog` |\n\nWhen `PASS` verdict is issued and active P2 findings remain, set `hasAdvisories = true` in the report metadata.\n\n#### Step 6: Finalize State\n\n1. Update config status: Set `status: \"complete\"` in `deep-review-config.json`\n2. Write final JSONL entry:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"type\": \"event\",\n     \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n     \"mode\": \"review\",\n     \"totalIterations\": N,\n     \"verdict\": \"PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\",\n     \"activeP0\": N,\n     \"activeP1\": N,\n     \"activeP2\": N,\n     \"dimensionCoverage\": X,\n     \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n     \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 5. PHASE 4: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\n\nPreserve review context to the memory system for future session recovery and cross-session continuity.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Generate context**: Run the memory save script with the spec folder:\n   ```bash\n   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}\n   ```\n\n2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow.\n\n3. **Verify**: Confirm `memory/*.md` file was created with proper anchors.\n\n### On Save Failure\n\nIf memory save fails:\n- Preserve the current `review/` packet as backup (the disk state is the ground truth)\n- Log the error\n- The review results remain intact in `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` regardless of memory save status\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUTO-RESUME PROTOCOL\n\n### Purpose\n\nEnable review sessions to resume cleanly from prior state when interrupted by context compaction, process termination, or intentional pause.\n\n### Resume Detection\n\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n\n1. **Verify agreement**: Confirm config, JSONL, findings registry, and strategy all exist and agree on target/spec folder\n2. **Count progress**: Read JSONL, count iteration records, determine last completed iteration\n3. **Read strategy**: Load current dimension progress, findings, and next focus from `deep-review-strategy.md`\n4. **Set counter**: Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. **Log resume**: Append the canonical resume event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The reducer requires every field below:\n   ```json\n   {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-24T14:05:00Z\"}\n   ```\n6. **Continue**: Enter the iteration loop from step_read_state\n\n### Lifecycle Branches (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures. Until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `review/` tree moved under `review_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus non-null `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n### State Validation on Resume\n\n| Condition | Classification | Action |\n|-----------|---------------|--------|\n| Config + JSONL + strategy all exist and agree | `resume` | Continue from last iteration + 1 |\n| All exist, config says `status: \"complete\"` | `completed-session` | Report completion, ask user if re-review desired |\n| Partial files or contradictions | `invalid-state` | Halt for repair, do not guess |\n| No files exist | `fresh` | Start new initialization |\n\n### State Recovery Cascade\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation |\n| 2 | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract dimensions, findings, coverage |\n| 3 | JSONL missing, iteration files exist | Scan `review/iterations/iteration-*.md`, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase |\n| 5 | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PAUSE/RESUME\n\n### Pause Sentinel Behavior\n\nThe pause sentinel provides graceful loop suspension in autonomous mode without killing the process.\n\n### Creating a Pause\n\nCreate the sentinel file at any time:\n\n```bash\ntouch {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n```\n\nThe orchestrator checks for this file between iterations (Step 2a). When detected:\n- The current iteration is allowed to complete\n- The loop halts before dispatching the next iteration\n- A paused event is logged to JSONL\n- The user is notified with current state (iteration count, dimensions covered, findings)\n\n### Resuming After Pause\n\nDelete the sentinel file and restart the workflow:\n\n```bash\nrm {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n```\n\nOn the next invocation:\n- The auto-resume protocol (Section 6) detects the existing state\n- A resumed event is logged to JSONL\n- The loop continues from the next iteration\n\n### Confirm Mode Approval Gates\n\nIn confirm mode (`deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml`), the workflow adds explicit approval gates instead of relying on the pause sentinel:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config, strategy, and scope. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings, dashboard, and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final review-report.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS, ERROR HANDLING, AND QUALITY GATES\n\nState-transition rules, error handling, and the review quality gates live in `loop_state_and_gates.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Shared Protocol Documentation\n\nProtocol documents from `deep-research` are cross-referenced, not duplicated:\n\n| Document | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Loop Protocol (research) | `../deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` | Research loop lifecycle (this file adapts Section 9) |\n| State Format | `../deep-research/references/state/state_format.md` | JSONL, strategy, and config schemas |\n| Convergence | `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` | `shouldContinue_review()` (Section 10), stuck recovery, quality guards |\n\n### Review-Specific Resources\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n| Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n| Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n| Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n\n### Workflow Files\n\n| Mode | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` |\n\n### Agent\n\n| Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n\nRuntime paths:\n- OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n- Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n- Codex: `.codex/agents/deep-review.toml`\n\n---\n\n## Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n\n### Invariants\n\nEvery executor path MUST satisfy:\n\n1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n\n### Failure Modes\n\n- Missing iteration file: `iteration_file_missing` from `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event.\n- Empty iteration file: `iteration_file_empty`, same downstream.\n- JSONL not appended: `jsonl_not_appended`.\n- JSONL missing required fields: `jsonl_missing_fields`.\n- JSONL malformed: `jsonl_parse_error`.\n- 3 consecutive failures: existing `stuck_recovery` event (unchanged).\n\n### JSONL Audit Field\n\nNon-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n\n### Template And Config Surface\n\nThe executor-agnostic iteration prompt lives at `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, rendered by `prompt-pack.ts` before dispatch and either injected as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\n\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\n\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\n\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":756,"totalLines":756,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1780906975605,"end":1780906975629}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_026bcb7bde4a4d56016a267bdf83b88191b7939ec6b9ba59cb"}},"id":"prt_ea653e160001E5YrWcIDA0u53W","sessionID":"ses_159adeef9ffepPqSo0MVC5zQx7","messageID":"msg_ea65391be001soWxilxpMDrfUs"}}
